"""
Fused HUD  —  Camera + YOLOv8n  ×  BGT60TR13C Radar
====================================================
One window, three panels:
  [ CAMERA + YOLO feed ]  [ Radar polar scope ]  [ Sidebar: targets / range profile / system ]

Low-light logic:
  - Radar targets are projected onto the camera panel by angle. If a YOLO
    box overlaps that column -> drawn in the "confirmed" accent color.
    If not -> drawn in magenta as "RADAR-ONLY", meaning the radar sees
    something the camera/YOLO currently can't (e.g. low light).

This keeps your original radar HUD's visual language (topbar / sidebar /
target cards / range profile / polar scope) and adds a camera panel that
runs YOLO in its own thread, feeding the same window.

Dependencies:
    pip install pygame numpy opencv-python ultralytics gpiozero lgpio
Run from the same folder as your existing utility/ and radar_config/.
"""

